# Next.js frontend (`apps/frontend`)

For **ESLint, Prettier, tests, and dev-server restarts**, use `quokkaq-agent-workflow.mdc`. This rule covers **structure and patterns** only.

## Stack

- Next.js 16+ (App Router), React 19, TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui (Radix), TanStack Query, next-intl, Zod

## Routing and locale

- App routes live under [`app/[locale]/`](apps/frontend/app/[locale]/); zones use their own `layout.tsx` where the repo already does.
- Locale and API rewrites: root [`proxy.ts`](apps/frontend/proxy.ts) (Next 16; not legacy `middleware.ts`).

## Data and API

- Prefer TanStack Query plus helpers in [`lib/api.ts`](apps/frontend/lib/api.ts). Avoid one-off `fetch` to the API base that bypasses established patterns.

## UI

- Reuse `components/ui` and existing layout/sidebar patterns before adding new primitives.

## i18n

- User-visible strings: `next-intl` keys under [`messages/`](apps/frontend/messages/). Add keys in both locales when the project already mirrors `en` / `ru`.

## React / ESLint

- Follow [`eslint.config.mjs`](apps/frontend/eslint.config.mjs) (Next core-web-vitals + TypeScript + Prettier flat config). Respect hook-related rules (e.g. avoid problematic synchronous `setState` in `useEffect`); prefer patterns already used in the codebase (remount/`key`, derived state).

